	" Stage 3
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This is where the stair glitch comes in.
	$LF
	"Using some strategic wiggling, I can exit the staircase and make it directly to the boss without having to get the white key.
	$LF
	"Not only is this much faster, but it also skips the door opening animation, which is also a nice bonus.
	$LF
	"The stair glitch here saves over 10 seconds.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=BossVampireBat 
	" Boss: Vampire Bat
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Better understanding of the boss's behavior allowed me to use a faster strategy against it.
	$LF
	"When the bat appears, it will wait for a certain amount of time and then fly down to a specific position that is determined by your own position on the screen.
	$LF
	"After that, the bat will wait between 64 and 128 frames, which is determined by RNG, and then swoop down towards you.
	$LF
	"I specifically manipulate the bat to wait as short as possible, so that it swoops down to me after just two jumps.
	$LF
	"When the bat begins to move, I make sure to move as close to it as possible so that its own horizontal speed is as slow as possible.
	$LF
	"This allows me to simply walk away from it and then leisurely whip it down while on the ground.
	$LF
	"It might seem slow to have to walk away first, but whipping from the ground is significantly faster than having to jump to reach it, and also avoids needing to jump over it to avoid the swoop, which results in a net gain of 27 frames against the boss.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Overall, 672 frames were saved in Level 1.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Stage4 
	" Stage 4
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Another stair glitch is used as a shortcut to get to the key, although the armor knight in this area is a real nuisance.
	$LF
	"This is the fastest way I found to deal with it.
	$LF
	"I grab the stopwatch in this level from a convenient treasure chest.
	$LF
	"There are two keys in the level that I could pick up to open the chest, but the second one is slightly faster.
	$LF
	"All in all, picking up the stopwatch here loses me 117 frames, but it more than makes up that time later.
	$LF
]div
