]div
[div class=p 
	"I pick up the boots in this stage again.
	$LF
	"I determined that they should save maybe some 13 frames throughout the remainder of the stage, as almost the entire rest is spent climbing stairs, but hey, it's still a timesave.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I use a stair glitch to get from the key to the door quickly.
	$LF
	"I kill a hunchback with a knife to get a big heart from it.
	$LF
	"This is technically suboptimal, as it's not necessary to kill the hunchback, and the knife causes some lag, so I should've gotten the heart earlier, but I wasn't gonna go back to redo this stage and the previous one.
	$LF
	"All in all, this loses me between 4 - 6 frames.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Overall, the new route still ends up saving a sweet 976 frames, so I'm not complaining too much.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=BossDracula 
	" Boss: Dracula
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Dracula's first phase is pretty much entirely unchanged to before.
	$LF
	"I need to unfreeze time at some point to get him to appear, but once his hurtbox is active, I can once again just stick him in place and spam knives into him in a way that would make Dio blush.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It would be better if I could use the stopwatch just once, as I have to ride out the second use before his second phase appears, but I couldn't find a way to dispatch him in just 1 cycle.
	$LF
	"You're just 2 knives short.
	$LF
	"It seems Dracula's second form will only appear after all of his debris have left the screen, but there seems to be no way to manipulate them, so I'm stuck with this pattern.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I took two additional big hearts with me for Dracula's second phase for 3 stopwatch uses total, so I don't have to deal with his bats at all, which saves another 60 frames.
	$LF
	"The game is just always better when it's not bothering you.
	$LF
	"With the final knife throw, input ends, and the game is over yet again.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=ClosingComments 
	" Closing Comments
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"And that was the fourth iteration of Vampire Killer.
	$LF
	"I am quite happy with some of the new strategies I found, but I have to admit that the stopwatch glitch seriously dampens entertainment in a lot of places.
	$LF
	"As mentioned earlier, the stopwatch glitch basically creates two radically different versions of the run.
	$LF
	"However, I am against creating a separate branch for this movie, as you still go through the same levels in largely the same way as before.
	$LF
	"The previous publication is at this point also severely outdated now and should be obsoleted.
	$LF
	"I also don't have any new findings that would've been unique to the non-stopwatch glitch route, which means a new regular run would be largely unchanged to before, save for what you can see in this TAS.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Despite this, there's still a bunch of loose ends that are worth investigating.
	$LF
	"I do not think this game is maxed out by a long shot.
	$LF
	"The stopwatch glitch saves "only" 13 seconds, so any new tech that would be exclusive to the regular route could put that back into the spotlight again.
	$LF
	"If you are interested in looking at this game, here is some potential areas that might turn out fruitful:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" General route and strategy improvements. E.g., you might possibly grab a shield in Stage 17 to block Dracula's fireballs, which could allow you to finish his first phase with only one stopwatch usage. I didn't try this out, but it might be worthwhile.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Find a faster way to activate the stair glitch
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Find a way to carry a stair glitch through screen transitions
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Find a shortcut to the door in Stage 8 while time is frozen
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Find a shortcut to the key in Stage 10
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Find a way to carry items through level changes
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Furthermore, if you try hard enough, you might still be able to save a few frames from better lag and optimization in various places. 
	$LF
	"As mentioned above, I also lose 6 frames from having to grab an extra big heart.
	$LF
	"I should've picked up more small hearts to max out my heart count before getting to the merchant in Stage 13, which would've allowed me to avoid this time loss.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Still, I hope that you enjoy watching the run.
	$LF
	"It was unexpectedly enjoyable and energizing to make, and made me rethink if I am really as "retired" from this hobby as I thought I was.
	$LF
	"Special thanks naturally go out once again to the openMSX crew, in particular Quibus, Vampier and wouterv for answering my (sometimes dumb) questions.
	$LF
	"Their work on openMSX has been phenomenal.
	$LF
	"The emulator now features a GUI that made working with it a lot easier.
	$LF
	"I would also like to thank Burb and AgentWyvern for their findings on this game and their support.
	$LF
	"They did a huge part to (re-)vitalize the Vampire Killer speedrunning scene, and without them, I probably wouldn't have been making this run.
	$LF
	"I also cross-referenced their routes heavily while making this run to make sure I was on the right track.
	$LF
